---
import SectionHeading from '../ui/SectionHeading.astro';
---

<section class="gb-section" data-galaxy-state="engines" aria-labelledby="agnostic-title">
	<div class="gb-container gb-split">
		<div>
			<SectionHeading
				kicker="Swappable by design"
				title="Adding an engine is one registration line."
				lede="Engines implement a Rust EngineAdapter trait behind a strategy pattern — no call sites change when one joins. The SDK types each mount by its real capabilities, so impossible operations fail at compile time, not in production."
				id="agnostic-title"
			/>
			<ul class="gb-checklist" role="list">
				<li><strong>Capability-typed SDK</strong> — a Redis mount that can't subscribe is a type error, not a 3 a.m. incident.</li>
				<li><strong>Honest descriptors</strong> — every mount advertises exactly what it supports; the planner refuses the rest with a clean 403.</li>
				<li><strong>Same authorization everywhere</strong> — ABAC, field-level masks and owner-scoping run in the data plane, not per-engine.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<div>
			<pre class="gb-code"><code><span class="c">// the same app, three different engines</span>
<span class="k">const</span> orders  = grobase.<span class="f">mount</span>(<span class="s">'pg-commerce'</span>)
<span class="k">const</span> metrics = grobase.<span class="f">mount</span>(<span class="s">'mysql-ops'</span>)
<span class="k">const</span> events  = grobase.<span class="f">mount</span>(<span class="s">'mongo-activity'</span>)

<span class="k">await</span> orders.<span class="f">table</span>(<span class="s">'orders'</span>).<span class="f">list</span>({'{'} status: <span class="s">'paid'</span> {'}'})
<span class="k">await</span> events.<span class="f">table</span>(<span class="s">'clicks'</span>).<span class="f">insert</span>(payload)

<span class="c">// capability honesty: this is a COMPILE error</span>
<span class="c">// on a mount whose descriptor says stream: false</span>
events.<span class="f">subscribe</span>(<span class="s">'clicks'</span>, onChange)</code></pre>
			<p class="gb-code-note">Owner-scoping is automatic: rows are stamped with the caller's principal; other tenants never see them.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
